{
  "id": "ex_technical_8eec0a9d",
  "source_file": "sci-amplex-red.ot2.apiv2.py",
  "intent_precise": "Amplex Red Hydrogen Peroxide Assay: Using falcontubes (tuberack, slot 11), tubes1 (tuberack, slot 7), tubes2 (tuberack, slot 5), plate (plate, slot 7). With temperature module. (1) Transfer from source to destination. (2) Transfer 200\u00b5L from falcontubes A1 to falcontubes A3. (3) Mix 2 times at 200\u00b5L in falcontubes A3. (4) Transfer 200\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 to tubes1 A1. (5) Transfer 177\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 to tubes1 A1. (6) Transfer 23\u00b5L from tubes1 D3 to tubes1 A1. (7) Mix 2 times at 200\u00b5L in tubes1 A1. (8) Distribute 200\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 to tubes1 wells A1-B6 (5 wells). (9) Transfer 50\u00b5L from tubes1 A1 to tubes1 B4. (10) Mix 2 times at 200\u00b5L in tubes1 B4. (11) Transfer 50\u00b5L from tubes1 B4 to tubes1 B5. (12) Mix 2 times at 200\u00b5L in tubes1 B5. (13) Transfer 100\u00b5L from tubes1 B5 to tubes1 B6. (14) Mix 2 times at 200\u00b5L in tubes1 B6. (15) Transfer from tubes1 B6 to tubes1 A1. (16) Mix wells A3-B3 (7 wells) in tubes1, 3 cycles at 150\u00b5L. (17) Transfer 200\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 to falcontubes B1. (18) Transfer 140\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 to falcontubes B1. (19) Transfer 40\u00b5L from tubes1 D4 to falcontubes B1. (20) Transfer 20\u00b5L from tubes1 D5 to falcontubes B1. (21) Mix 3 times at 200\u00b5L in falcontubes B1. (22) Wait 0 seconds. (23) Wait 0 seconds. (24) Wait 1 seconds. (25) Transfer from falcontubes A3 to tubes2 A1. (26) Transfer 10\u00b5L from tubes2 A1 to tubes2 A2. (27) Mix 2 times at 100\u00b5L in tubes2 A2. (28) Transfer 10\u00b5L from tubes2 A2 to tubes2 A3. (29) Mix 2 times at 100\u00b5L in tubes2 A3. (30) Distribute from falcontubes A3 to tubes1 wells A1-A1 (4 wells). (31) Mix wells C2-D1 (6 wells) in tubes1, 2 cycles at 200\u00b5L. (32) Wait 0 seconds. (33) Wait 0 seconds. (34) Wait 1 seconds. (35) Wait 0 seconds. (36) Wait 0 seconds. (37) Wait 1 seconds. (38) Set temperature to 37\u00b0C.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform 2 distribution steps, temperature control (37\u00b0C). (volumes 10\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~7 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Amplex Red Hydrogen Peroxide Assay, you'll need to set up your tube racks with falcontubes in slot 11, tubes1 in slot 7, and tubes2 in slot 5, plus the plate in slot 7 with the temperature module. Start by transferring 200\u00b5L from falcontubes A1 to A3, mix twice at 200\u00b5L, then prepare your working solution in tubes1 A1 by adding 200\u00b5L and 177\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 plus 23\u00b5L from tubes1 D3, mixing twice at 200\u00b5L. Create your serial dilutions by transferring 50\u00b5L from tubes1 A1 to B4 (mix twice), then 50\u00b5L to B5 (mix twice), and finally 100\u00b5L to B6 (mix twice), followed by distributing 200\u00b5L from falcontubes A3 to tubes1 wells A1-B6. Prepare your detection reagent in falcontubes B1 by combining 200\u00b5L and 140\u00b5L from A3 with 40\u00b5L from tubes1 D4 and 20\u00b5L from D5, mix three times, then set up your final dilution series in tubes2 (10\u00b5L transfers from A1 to A2 to A3 with mixing), and finish by setting the temperature module to 37\u00b0C.",
